
[1]reverberatory

   REVERB'ERATORY, a. Returning or driving back; as a reverberatory
   furnace or kiln.

   REVERB'ERATORY, n. A furnace with a kind of dome that reflects the
   flame upon a vessel placed within it, so as to surround it.
